00:55:47.150 --> 00:55:48.200
But when you opened with--

00:55:48.200 --> 00:55:50.158
RICHARD SCHMALENSEE: But
you're on team B here.

00:55:50.158 --> 00:55:51.780
I mean, I'm sorry, we need--

00:55:51.780 --> 00:55:52.610
we need you with--

00:55:52.610 --> 00:55:53.120
OK.

00:55:53.120 --> 00:55:53.720
AUDIENCE: When you opened--

00:55:53.720 --> 00:55:55.262
RICHARD SCHMALENSEE:
Support Cardozo.

00:55:55.262 --> 00:55:55.940
I was joking.

00:55:55.940 --> 00:55:57.410
You don't have to be
socialist, over here.

00:55:57.410 --> 00:55:57.611
AUDIENCE: No, it's fine.

00:55:57.611 --> 00:55:58.400
But when you opened it,
then I was like, wow,

00:55:58.400 --> 00:56:01.430
there are more correlations
